description:
Gender - Province of Residence in Pakistan
The Census of Afghans shows that there are 548,105 Afghan families, comprising 3,049,268 individuals
currently residing in Pakistan. This gives the family size of 5.6 persons on the average.
The census of Afghans, undertaken in all locations in Pakistan, shows that 548,105 Afghan
families, comprising 3,049,268 individuals currently reside in Pakistan. This census presents
the clearest quantitative and qualitative demographic data to date on Afghans in Pakistan.
The numbers may be surprising to some, considering the return of over 2.3 million Afghans
since March 2002, the implication being that more than 5 million Afghans were in Pakistan at
the time of the fall of the Taliban.
